About the business
Jenike & Johanson (Jenike) is recognized as the world’s leading authority for reliable and efficient bulk solids handling and processing. We have an international clientele that includes many Fortune 100 companies from industries including: chemicals, cement, mining, minerals, foods, power/energy, plastics, and pharmaceuticals.
Such diversification provides for an interesting and rewarding career, developing unique, cost-effective solutions to a wide range of engineering challenges in the world. Our company is 100% employee owned, with all employees having the opportunity to participate in an excellent benefits package (benefits may vary by location).
About the role
The primary purpose of a Jenike project engineer is to effectively execute on a wide range of engineering assignments to ensure our clients’ needs are satisfied and they’re thrilled with the results. A Jenike project engineer is required to:
Execute efficiently on bulk material handling consulting projects;
Identify and develop project scope and proposal for award of project;
Communicate (written and oral) effectively with all staff, clients, and suppliers;
Rapidly learn, apply, and retain vital bulk solids handling knowledge and practices;
Propagate a total safety and team support culture;
Live the corporate values of
ownership
,
excellence
, and
integrity
; and,
Participate in other duties, as directed.
Benefits and perks
A rare opportunity for an early career engineer to join one of the world’s great science-based consultancies offering:
Opportunity to grow into world-class expert in bulk material handling;
Small team environment;
Teaching and application ecosystem;
Periodic off-site travel to meet with clients;
Comprehensive training plan and growth pathway to senior roles;
A benefits package, including profit sharing, extended health care (prescriptions, dental), LTD, critical illness and life insurance coverage.
Requirements
Only those who meet all selection criteria below will be considered for this important role.
ACHIEVEMENT
of an accredited four-year degree in mechanical, chemical, or civil engineering – an advanced degree is not required, but is preferred;
PASSION
for building a long-term career in bulk material handling science;
PROBLEM-SOLVING
skills and sound analytical capabilities;
PROJECT EXECUTION
in a timely and accurate manner to meet deadlines;
TEAM PLAYER
performance within a multi-disciplinary, global group;
LEARNER
with an energetic curiosity;
DILIGENCE
and demonstration of ability to “go the extra mile;” and,
EXPERIENCE
in professional engineering employment of at least two years (time during internship not included).
If you feel that you are a strong candidate and can demonstrate that you would be a “good fit” for the project engineer position in
Toronto, Canada
, please email your resume and cover letter to “Recruiting department” at Jobs_Toronto@jenike.com .

We are Pomerleau. And you could be too.
Pomerleau is recognized as one of Canada’s leaders in the construction industry, in the institutional, commercial, industrial and civil engineering sectors. Clients benefit from our expertise as general contractor, construction manager, project manager and design-builder.
Pomerleau believes in delivering excellence. Every Pomerleau employee upholds this value, leading to the achievement of superior results in every sector where we do business. Pomerleau: proud individuals who share a vision and are passionate about what they do.
What YOU Will Do
Design, handle, and perform the follow-up and the approval of special equipment and special tools intended with the construction methods;
Analyze the various plans and specs;
Draw up the list of project requirements with regard to temporary equipment and structures;
Put together the preliminary work schedule;
Develop manpower curves relating to the schedule;
Take part in the transfer meeting with the production team;
Confirm and finalize construction methods with the construction team;
Put together various documents, namely construction site installation plans as well as the plans which are specific to the project;
Design temporary structures—formwork, envelope, access, etc.;
Sign and seal construction plans;
Provide technical support to the production team on construction sites.
What YOU Will Bring
Bachelor’s degree in civil engineering or in construction engineering;
Member of Engineers and Geoscientist BC;
5+ years’ experience in the civil construction industry;
Marine experience considered an asset;
Solid written and verbal communication skills;
Strong computer skills with enthusiasm for innovation;
Excellent analytical skills and sound technical knowledge;
Proficiency in Excel, AutoCAD, MS Project, Primavera, Civil 3D, Advance Design America, Revit software;
Ability to exercise initiative and promote the quest for results.
Why Choose Pomerleau
Competitive salary
4 weeks’ vacation
Group insurance (including a health spending account!)
Group RRSP
Employer paid monthly public transit pass
Fitness Membership or Activity Reimbursement
Employee assistance program
Exciting training opportunities
Dynamic culture
Exciting career opportunities
Summer hours
What are you waiting for? Let's build something extraordinary together. Apply now to join the team. We want to hear from you!
We thank all applicants, but only those selected for further consideration will be contacted. Be sure to join our Talent Network to stay informed about all job opportunities at Pomerleau.
Pomerleau Inc. is an equal opportunity employer. We are committed to providing employment accommodation in accordance with the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act. During any stage of the recruitment and hiring process, accommodation for applicants with disabilities are available upon request.

Environmental/Civil Engineer
Professional opportunity for a well-motivated environmental/civil engineer with a B.S. or M.S. degree, intern or work experience a plus. The successful candidate will work on a range of environmental projects, including as part of an interdisciplinary team on some highly complex remediation projects.
Preferred skills include:
Water resources management – hydrology (riverine/estuary), hydrogeology, and water treatment;
Interdisciplinary training and sustainability analysis skills preferred;
Strong analytical approach to problem analysis, data management and problem solving, using software tools (e.g., GIS, CAD) and modeling;
Technology and alternatives evaluation, interest in remedial design a plus;
Knowledge of the environmental regulatory framework; and
High level of communication capabilities, organization and technical writing.
This position provides a substantial opportunity for professional growth and advancement.
The ELM Group, Inc. (ELM) is an employee-owned firm celebrating 30+ years of environmental consulting and engineering. ELM emphasizes pragmatic and sustainable solutions and a holistic understanding of environmental problems. ELM supports continuing education and training towards completion of a P.E.
ELM offers signing incentives, competitive salary, excellent benefits (including a 401K with company match), continuing education and an Employee Stock Ownership Plan (ESOP). Positions in the Princeton, NJ and Holicong (Doylestown), PA offices.
Send resume to HR@elminc.com, please reference ELM-Engineer in the subject line. EOE.
